If you want to learn about why it can be difficult to match prints to the images you see on your computer or phone, this course is very helpful and I learned a lot. But if you're a photographer looking for practical advice on a good digital printing workflow, this course comes up short.

The course seems to be made by a print operator who has a lot of experience on how to get his colors right.
However a lot of the processes, techniques, and essentials that are very important to color management are not discussed at all or discussed without any visuals and therefore lacking substance to really understand the matter.
Main points I'm missing most are: DeltaE, Color Gamut, Gamma, Rendering Intents.

This course might only be of any help if you are printing for yourself and find the colors are somewhat off from expectation, or if you have some kind of real world reference you can compare the colors to.

If you're planning on using a online printing service, with this course, you will not learn anything on how to prepare your documents in order to get the results you expect.

You will also not be able to reproduce correct color, if you are printing a document and don't have a reference to compare it's color to.
